# Contributing to *The Cycle of Fire and Ice*

Welcome to the shared storytelling universe *The Cycle of Fire and Ice* — a world where magic causes civilization-ending ice ages, and every story adds depth to the lore.

This is a collaborative world open to writers, artists, screenwriters, and creators of all kinds. All stories and additions must follow canon and use the shared CC BY-SA 4.0 license.

---

## 📝 Publish Stories on Medium

All stories, comics, and screenplays should be published on **[Medium.com](https://medium.com/)** under your own account.

### Your story must:
- Credit the universe:
  > *This story is part of the shared universe The Cycle of Fire and Ice.*
- Include the license notice:
  > *Licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/*
- Optionally link back to the [GitHub wiki](https://github.com/NumaPepi/The-Cycle-of-Fire-And-Ice/wiki)

---

## 📚 Submit Lore to the Wiki

If your story introduces or expands world elements (races, artifacts, magical principles, etc.), you’re encouraged to:

- Add or edit a page in the GitHub [Wiki](https://github.com/NumaPepi/The-Cycle-of-Fire-And-Ice/wiki)
- Link to your Medium story at the top or bottom of the wiki page
- Stay consistent with existing canon (or propose new branches clearly)

---

## ✍️ What You Can Add to the Wiki

- Lore about your story’s setting, character, or culture
- Magical theories, spells, and limitations
- New creatures, races, or lost Ages of Man (pre First Age)
- Timelines, maps, or historical events
- Transcriptions of story summaries (no full stories)

---

## ⚖️ License

All contributions must follow the [CC BY-SA 4.0 License](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/).

> This means others can reuse and adapt your work — with credit — and must share their version under the same terms.

---

## 💬 Need Help?

- Visit the [Wiki](https://github.com/NumaPepi/The-Cycle-of-Fire-And-Ice/wiki)
- File an [Issue](https://github.com/NumaPepi/The-Cycle-of-Fire-And-Ice/issues) with your questions or ideas
- Or contact John Pepin directly: john.pepin@hotmail.com

---

## 🌍 Join the Cycle

Publish on Medium.  
Add your lore to the wiki.  
Help build a living, breathing world — together.
